I have always believed that Ethiopia’s waste disposal crisis doesn’t require a miracle, but a persistent mind willing to solve the problem from the inside out. I used to define leadership as relying on my own individual effort, but seeing my team’s dedication during one lunchtime of solo work taught me that my true role was to create a space where every member could participate and contribute. I organized collaborative sessions where everyone could bring ideas and share them with others, learning that leadership means empowering the team rather than doing everything myself. To make the project meaningful, I led a community survey, understanding how the national plastic bag ban affected local vendors and families, while sharing our progress on a biodegradable alternative. This experience taught me that true leadership is about guiding, motivating, and creating impact through teamwork.
